{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"87f6fd1b-7325-4649-bf79-129735169fc7","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nKey differences: xUnit embeds the skip reason in `[Fact]`/`[Theory]` itself rather than using a separate attribute. The others use standalone attributes alongside `[TestMethod]`/`[Test]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4f752d2b-73dc-476c-92be-335040276e93","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":334,"requestId":"4C11:2BC959:AE1456:D9EADF:6A012D4F"},"id":"c776c15a-a198-41a6-95d8-a53a4a7038fc","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:13:58.303Z","parentId":"0aa4410e-df7c-469d-a1ca-ca42f0316d7a"}
